{"id":"0903.5508","submitter":"Jose Manuel Velhinho","authors":"Jer\\'onimo Cortez, Guillermo A. Mena Marug\\'an, Rog\\'erio Ser\\^odio,\n  Jos\\'e M. Velhinho","title":"Uniqueness of the Fock quantization of a free scalar field on $S^1$ with\n  time dependent mass","comments":"13 pages, typos corrected, version accepted for publication in\n  Physical Review D","journal-ref":null,"doi":"10.1103/PhysRevD.79.084040","report-no":null,"categories":"gr-qc hep-th math-ph math.MP","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  We analyze the quantum description of a free scalar field on the circle in\nthe presence of an explicitly time dependent potential, also interpretable as a\ntime dependent mass. Classically, the field satisfies a linear wave equation of\nthe form $\\ddot{\\xi}-\\xi\"+f(t)\\xi=0$. We prove that the representation of the\ncanonical commutation relations corresponding to the particular case of a\nmassless free field ($f=0$) provides a unitary implementation of the dynamics\nfor sufficiently general mass terms, $f(t)$. Furthermore, this representation\nis uniquely specified, among the class of representations determined by\n$S^1$-invariant complex structures, as the only one allowing a unitary\ndynamics. These conclusions can be extended in fact to fields on the two-sphere\npossessing axial symmetry. This generalizes a uniqueness result previously\nobtained in the context of the quantum field description of the Gowdy\ncosmologies, in the case of linear polarization and for any of the possible\ntopologies of the spatial sections.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 31 Mar 2009 15:57:55 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 23 Apr 2009 14:40:10 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-05-13"}
